From: Jason Germino <jasongermino@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 11 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] cmake: enable position-independent code globally

LLVM static libraries are compiled without -fPIC by default, but
LLVM_BUILD_LLVM_DYLIB=ON (set by Buildroot's llvm.mk) links them all
into libLLVM.so. The linker rejects the resulting non-PIC relocations:

  R_X86_64_TPOFF32 (local-exec TLS) and R_X86_64_PC32 (vtables)
  can not be used when making a shared object; recompile with -fPIC

Setting CMAKE_POSITION_INDEPENDENT_CODE globally after project() causes
cmake to add -fPIC to all compilations, making the static library objects
safe to link into shared libraries.
---
 CMakeLists.txt | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/CMakeLists.txt b/CMakeLists.txt
--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -46,0 +46,2 @@
+
+set(CMAKE_POSITION_INDEPENDENT_CODE ON)
